    "However, LLMs can give different responses to the same prompts and there is a way to avoid this.",
    "To overcome this critical issue, the set of adopted prompts is made available online and as the possible answer only the \"yes\" or \"not\" are evaluated.",
    "This makes the experiments more repetible and reduces the differences due to how questions or commands are phrased.",
    "Moreover, we performed multiple runs along the experiment to ensure the correctness of the answer.Finally, referring to the external validity, we will focus on ensuring the generalizability of our results by extending the experimentation on a larger number of process models.",
    "ConclusionIn this paper, we introduced BPLLM, a novel methodology aimed at enabling grounded conversations with a LLM to enhance process-aware DSSs."
